WEBVTT

00:00.065 --> 00:02.125
Previously onThe Originals...
When the spell is over,

00:02.175 --> 00:03.525
you got to get away
from each other,

00:03.565 --> 00:05.045
and you have to stay away
from Hope.

00:05.085 --> 00:06.485
So the evil is
separated for all time.

00:06.525 --> 00:08.305
A powerful seer
prophesied destruction.

00:08.355 --> 00:09.875
"And thou shall know the signs

00:09.925 --> 00:11.615
of blood from water,
vipers from the rivers."

00:11.665 --> 00:12.875
KLAUS: "Fire across the water,

00:12.925 --> 00:14.665
"monsoons from the sea.

00:14.705 --> 00:16.105
The death of all Firstborns."

00:16.145 --> 00:17.185
Freya, me.
Hope.

00:17.235 --> 00:19.325
This is the last time
we can do this.

00:19.365 --> 00:20.935
I'm gonna fix this for us.

00:20.975 --> 00:23.155
We have to save
always and forever.

00:23.195 --> 00:25.155
I'd really like your help.
Anything you need.

00:25.195 --> 00:26.765
He let Hayley die!
She thought Elijah

00:26.805 --> 00:28.195
was there for her,
but he wasn't.

00:28.245 --> 00:30.375
[neck snaps]
[gasps]

00:30.415 --> 00:31.205
This is revenge.

00:31.245 --> 00:32.555
I'm taking great pleasure

00:32.595 --> 00:33.945
knowing she'll suffer.

00:33.985 --> 00:35.205
For a cure for Klaus's bite,
he wants to make a deal.

00:35.245 --> 00:36.815
Are you ready?
Open the red door.

00:36.865 --> 00:38.255
Remember your family.

00:38.295 --> 00:39.865
Remember Hayley!
[shouts]

00:39.905 --> 00:40.995
Why isn't he waking up?

00:41.035 --> 00:41.955
What the hell just happened?

00:41.995 --> 00:43.125
You better hope that he wakes up

00:43.175 --> 00:44.345
in time to get you this.

00:45.735 --> 00:47.135
ELIJAH: There's no way out.

00:47.175 --> 00:50.135
We're trapped here.

00:50.175 --> 00:53.965
KLAUS: In New Orleans,
bodies cannot be buried.

00:54.005 --> 00:56.705
Instead, in boxes above the ground,

00:56.745 --> 00:58.885
the dead cluster together.

00:58.925 --> 01:01.055
When a man passes on,

01:01.105 --> 01:04.015
his family tomb is cracked open.

01:04.065 --> 01:09.155
Old bones are shoved aside to
make room for fresh remains.

01:09.195 --> 01:13.115
Bloodlines rot, entangled.

01:14.985 --> 01:18.075
The houses are that way, too.

01:18.115 --> 01:20.685
Layer upon layer
of peeling paint,

01:20.735 --> 01:23.385
hiding little tragedies.

01:23.425 --> 01:25.695
Scorch marks from the fires.

01:25.735 --> 01:28.125
Waterlines on wallpaper.

01:28.175 --> 01:30.745
[thunder rumbling]

01:34.525 --> 01:38.315
These are the tombs
of the living,

01:38.355 --> 01:41.485
where we rot alongside
memories of our dead.

01:41.535 --> 01:42.795
[tinkling]

01:42.835 --> 01:44.845
Crowded with people
we have failed

01:44.885 --> 01:47.195
and those who have failed us,

01:47.235 --> 01:50.805
we are forced to struggle
with those we love.

01:50.845 --> 01:53.805
Every last exit is sealed.

01:53.855 --> 01:55.635
If you're thinking
about jumping, don't.

01:55.675 --> 01:57.115
I already tried it.

01:57.155 --> 01:58.945
I landed in the world's
most pretentious wine cellar.

01:58.985 --> 02:01.075
You sorted it by vintage.

02:02.515 --> 02:04.865
You don't remember, do you?

02:04.905 --> 02:07.865
I thought Marcel was intent
on retrieving your memories.

02:07.905 --> 02:09.475
He was. He failed.

02:09.514 --> 02:11.305
I still remember
absolutely nothing,

02:11.345 --> 02:12.695
and Antoinette is dying.

02:12.735 --> 02:15.745
Is she? Right.
Yes. I'd forgotten.

02:15.785 --> 02:18.095
What the hell are we doing here?
What is this place?

02:18.135 --> 02:19.965
This is dangerous,
you and I here together.

02:20.005 --> 02:22.225
We're not actually here
together, are we?

02:22.265 --> 02:24.405
Not physically, at least.
[sighs]

02:24.445 --> 02:26.315
It's called a Chambre de Chasse.

02:26.365 --> 02:28.845
It's a magical mental prison
designed to resemble our home.

02:28.885 --> 02:30.665
But don't worry.

02:30.715 --> 02:33.195
There's always a way out...
A game or a riddle.

02:33.235 --> 02:34.805
How do we solve this riddle?

02:34.845 --> 02:37.765
We don't do anything.

02:37.805 --> 02:39.855
We're square, you and I.

02:39.895 --> 02:41.635
You got Hayley killed,

02:41.685 --> 02:44.295
and Antoinette will die
because of me.

02:45.855 --> 02:48.465
I would hate to upset
that delicate balance.

02:48.515 --> 02:52.775
So I'm gonna find my way out,
and you're on your own.

